Doc Del,<br><br>
You are right, I would have interjected caution long before things got out of hand. In otherwords, long before Marc got involved. Months ago I urged that people stop calling names.<br><br>
A while back, I notified Marc that there was a problem with anonymous posters and that Barry Spatz had claimed that someone had posted in his name. Marc wrote me back and said that he hadn't been paying much attention to the site.<br><br>
Later, another poster notified Marc when a statement was posted that had mentioned &quot;scoring&quot; with a 13 year old girl.<br><br>
So, each time posters on this site had asked Marc to get involved. <br><br>
Yes, I agree that Marc can do whatever he likes with his site, and I feel that this site has been very beneficial.<br><br>
But, removal of the messages in question takes away from the continuity.<br><br>
Most times I have no trouble being civil. Some people do have trouble responding civilly when they are attacked. I even lost my composure for a while. No side of the argument is pristine in this matter. Therefore, the entire dialogue should be posted so that the entire account may be read.<br><br>
Cook is not asking that any of his words be removed, only that the words that provoked many of his responses be restored.
